article.description: — Keshawn Williams had 17 points in Northern Illinois' 90-70 victory over Eastern Illinois on Wednesday night.
article.headline: Williams scores 17 as Northern Illinois wins 90-70
article.linkText: Williams scores 17 as Northern Illinois wins 90-70
article.story: CHARLESTON, Ill. -- — Keshawn Williams had 17 points in Northern Illinois' 90-70 victory over Eastern Illinois on Wednesday night. Williams had five rebounds for the Huskies (3-5). David Coit scored 16 points and added five rebounds and five assists. Zarigue Nutter recorded 16 points and shot 4 of 5 from the field and 8 for 9 from the line. The Panthers (1-7) were led by Caleb Donaldson, who recorded 15 points and six assists. Eastern Illinois also got nine points from Dan Luers. In addition, Kyle Thomas had eight points. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
